The paper deals with the problem of quantization in compressed sensing, which is a fundamental issue in information theory (cs.IT). The proposed method involves using sigma-delta quantization, which is a common technique in signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method in compressing and decoding sparse and compressible signals, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also presents numerical experiments, which suggests that it may fall under the category of statistical learning (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
